Title: Skip housekeeping when repo is frozen (no commits, no ticket changes)
Status: open
Created: 2026-04-27
Author: claude

--- log ---
2026-04-27T12:30Z claude created

--- body ---
## Problem

`housekeeping_needed()` in `beat.py` only checks whether the last
housekeeping commit is older than the configured interval. A repo that
has had zero commits and zero ticket modifications since the last
housekeeping run still triggers a full Sonnet session, paying ~$0.40
to produce a STATE.md update that says "nothing changed".

## Solution

Extend `housekeeping_needed()` with a second condition: if the repo
is "frozen" (no new commits AND no ticket files modified since the last
housekeeping run), return False.

```python
def _repo_frozen_since(project: ProjectConfig, since: datetime) -> bool:
    # No commits since last hk
    log = subprocess.run(
        ["git", "-C", str(project.path), "log",
         f"--since={since.isoformat()}", "--oneline"],
        capture_output=True, text=True
    ).stdout.strip()
    if log:
        return False
    # No ticket files changed since last hk
    changed = subprocess.run(
        ["git", "-C", str(project.path), "diff", "--name-only",
         f"--diff-filter=M", f"HEAD@{{{since.isoformat()}}}"],
        capture_output=True, text=True
    ).stdout
    ticket_changed = any("tickets/" in line for line in changed.splitlines())
    return not ticket_changed
```

`housekeeping_needed()` calls `_repo_frozen_since(project, last_hk_time)`.
If frozen, log a skip reason and return False.

Note: ticket 0036 (skip if idle) may overlap — check before implementing.

## Acceptance criteria

- Housekeeping is skipped when `git log --since=<last_hk>` is empty AND
  no `tickets/` files were modified since last hk
- Skip is logged (beat log line or stdout) for observability
- `test_beat.py` covers the frozen-skip path
- Still runs normally when commits OR ticket changes are present
